                                        3220
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Open- domain dialogue systems, also known as chatbots, are designed to converse with and engage users on any topic with the aim of establishing, maintaining, and strengthening long- term relationships (Clark et al., 2019; Roller et al., 2020). Recently, open- domain dialogue systems built based on large- scale generative pre- trained models (Adiwardana et al., 2020; Roller et al., 2021; Zhang et al., 2020) have substantially improved the performance of chatbots."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
